(12, 48, 'Crabs', 'crabs', -1, 'true', '12', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify; &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;ï»¿&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;Crabs are members of the infra-order Brachyura and are characterized by their distinctive sideways&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;walking gait and their hard, exoskeletal shells. They are found in a wide range of aquatic habitats, from&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;freshwater rivers and lakes to brackish estuaries and the salty waters of the Bay of Bengal. In Bangladesh,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;there are 65 species of crabs under 2 orders and 30 families where the dominant family is Ocypodidae&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;which occupies 11 species. Other families include Portunidae 10 species, Xanthidae 5 species, Calappidae&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;and Sesarmidae 4 species, Matutidae 3 species, Gecarcinucidae, Grapsidae, Potamidae and Varunidae 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;species, Dromiidae, Carpiliidae, Coenobitidae, Diogenidae, Dotillidae, Dromiidae, Epialtidae, Epialtidae,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;Euryplacidae, Galenidae, Gecarcinidae, Inachidae, Leucosiidae, Majidae, Paguridae, Panopeidae,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;&quot;&gt;Limulidae, Porcellanidae, Zosiminae, Parapaguridae occupy 1 species each.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', 18, 6, 0, '2023-09-23 17:01:18'),
